Gluten Free Pie Crust
  --America's Test Kitchen

6 tbsp ice water
3 tbsp sour cream
1 tbsp rice vinegar
13 oz (2 3/4 c + 2 tbsp) atk ap gf flour
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp xanthan gum
16 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into 1/4" pieces and frozen for 10-15 min

Comibine ice water, sour cream, and vinegar together in bowl. Process flour blend, sugar, salt, and xanthan gum together in food processor until combined, ~5 s. Scatter butter over top and pulse until crumbs look uniform and distinct pieces of butter are no longer visible, 20-30 pulses. Divide dough into 2 even pieces. Turn each piece ofdough onto sheet of plastic wrap and flatten each into 5" disk. Wrap each piece tightly and refrigerate for at least 1 hr or up to 2 days. Before rolling out dough, let it sit on counter to soften slightly, ~ 30 m.
